{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YGGLnzuK9bkj58LDnB8Fxo","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a final comprehensive summary document. Here's everything you need:\n\n---\n\n## Backend Codebase Patterns Guide\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\nservices/backend/src/\n├── index.ts                 # Main app initialization (Hono setup, workers, routes)\n├── config.ts               # Environment var parsing & Config type\n├── db.ts                   # Database client (Postgres operations)\n├── db-config.ts            # Schema management utilities\n├── auth-db.ts              # Auth-specific DB operations (challenges, refresh tokens)\n├── logger.ts               # Structured JSON logger\n├── fairness.ts             # Fairness logic (secret generation, commitment)\n├── hono-env.ts             # Hono environment type definitions\n├── migrate.ts              # Migration runner\n├── tx-builder.ts           # Transaction building utilities\n├── middleware/             # HTTP middleware (JWT, rate-limit, auth)\n├── routes/                 # HTTP endpoint handlers (create, lord, closecall, etc.)\n├── worker/                 # Background workers (settlement, pda-watcher, retry, etc.)\n└── __tests__/              # Test files\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Postgres DB Client Usage\n\n**Import Pattern:**\n```typescript\nimport postgres from \"postgres\";  // from package.json: \"postgres\": \"^3.4.0\"\n```\n\n**Creation in index.ts:**\n```typescript\nconst sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);  // Returns: postgres.Sql instance\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);   // Wrapped client with typed queries\nconst authDb = createAuthDb(sql);          // Auth-specific operations\n```\n\n**Type Signature:**\n- `postgres(databaseUrl: string): postgres.Sql<{}>` — returns a typed query executor\n- Each query is executed via the backtick-template-literal syntax\n\n**Transaction Pattern (sql.begin):**\n```typescript\n// From migrate.ts:84-90\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  // tx is of type: postgres.TransactionSql (same interface as sql, but transactional)\n  await tx.unsafe(content);  // Run raw SQL with IF NOT EXISTS\n  await tx.unsafe(\n    \"INSERT INTO _migrations (version, name) VALUES ($1, $2)\",\n    [migration.version, migration.name],\n  );\n  // On function return: auto-commits. On error: auto-rollback.\n});\n```\n\n**Type of transaction handle `tx`:**\n- `type: postgres.TransactionSql` (extends `postgres.Sql`)\n- Supports the same methods: `` await tx`SQL template` ``, `.unsafe()`, `.json()`, etc.\n- Automatic rollback on error; auto-commit on success\n\n---\n\n### 3. INSERT Statement Pattern\n\n**Basic INSERT with RETURNING:**\n```typescript\n// From db.ts:310-328\nasync insertRound(params) {\n  const rows = await sql<Round[]>`\n    INSERT INTO rounds (pda, game, creator, server_key, secret, commitment, amount_lamports, side, match_id, phase, entries)\n    VALUES (\n      ${params.pda},\n      ${params.game},\n      ${params.creator},\n      ${params.serverKey},\n      ${params.secret},\n      ${params.commitment},\n      ${params.amountLamports},\n      ${params.side},\n      ${params.matchId},\n      ${params.phase},\n      ${params.entries ? sql.json(params.entries) : null}  // JSONB column\n    )\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return normalizeRound(rows[0]!);\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Type annotation: `` sql<Round[]>` `` — declares return type\n- Parameter interpolation: `${variable}` — automatically escaped\n- JSONB values: `sql.json(data)` — special handler for JSON columns\n- `null` values: pass directly as `${null}` or `sql.json(null)`\n- Return clause: `RETURNING *` to get inserted row\n\n**Batch INSERT:**\n```typescript\n// From db.ts:551-564\nasync insertTransactions(params) {\n  if (params.length === 0) return;\n  const values = params.map((p) => ({\n    wallet: p.wallet,\n    game: p.game,\n    match_id: p.matchId,\n    tx_type: p.txType,\n    amount_lamports: p.amountLamports,\n    tx_sig: p.txSig,\n  }));\n  await sql`\n    INSERT INTO transactions ${sql(values, \"wallet\", \"game\", \"match_id\", \"tx_type\", \"amount_lamports\", \"tx_sig\")}\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotent INSERT:**\n```typescript\n// From db.ts:536-548\nasync insertTransaction(params) {\n  await sql`\n    INSERT INTO transactions (wallet, game, match_id, tx_type, amount_lamports, tx_sig)\n    VALUES (\n      ${params.wallet},\n      ${params.game},\n      ${params.matchId},\n      ${params.txType},\n      ${params.amountLamports},\n      ${params.txSig}\n    )\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Worker Initialization Pattern (from index.ts)\n\n```typescript\n// Line 148-159\nconst worker = createSettlementWorker({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  serverKey: config.serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  pollIntervalMs: config.workerPollIntervalMs,\n  onSettleReady: async (pda) => {\n    await retrySettler.attemptSettle(pda);\n    pdaWatcher.unwatch(pda);\n  },\n  isFinalized: (pda) => retrySettler.isFinalized(pda),\n});\nworker.start();  // Workers start with .start() method\n\n// Close Call clock worker example (line 163-168)\nconst closeCallClock = createCloseCallClockWorker({\n  connection,\n  serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair,\n  db: sql,  // Note: can pass raw sql instance OR wrapped db\n});\ncloseCallClock.start();\n```\n\n**Worker interface pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport interface SettlementWorker {\n  start(): void;\n  stop(): void;\n  readonly isRunning: boolean;\n  poll(): Promise<void>;  // Exposed for testing\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Environment Variable Parsing (config.ts)\n\n**Pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Config {\n  port: number;\n  databaseUrl: string;\n  dbSchema: string;\n  rpcUrl: string;\n  wsRpcUrl: string | undefined;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  cluster: string;\n  challengeTtlSeconds: number;\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: number;\n  // ... more fields\n}\n\nfunction requireEnv(name: string): string {\n  const value = process.env[name];\n  if (!value) {\n    throw new Error(`Missing required environment variable: ${name}`);\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nexport function loadConfig(): Config {\n  const dbSchema = loadDbSchemaFromEnv();\n  return {\n    port: parseInt(process.env.PORT ?? \"3100\", 10),\n    databaseUrl: applyDbSchemaToUrl(requireEnv(\"DATABASE_URL\"), dbSchema),\n    rpcUrl: requireEnv(\"RPC_URL\"),\n    wsRpcUrl: process.env.WS_RPC_URL || undefined,\n    serverKeypair: parseKeypair(requireEnv(\"SERVER_KEYPAIR\")),\n    jwtSecret: (() => {\n      const explicit = process.env.JWT_SECRET;\n      if (explicit) return new TextEncoder().encode(explicit);\n      // Derive from first 32 bytes of server keypair\n      const kp = parseKeypair(requireEnv(\"SERVER_KEYPAIR\"));\n      return kp.secretKey.slice(0, 32);\n    })(),\n    // ... defaults for all fields\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Use `requireEnv(name)` for mandatory vars (throws if missing)\n- Use `process.env.VAR ?? \"default\"` for optional vars\n- Parse numerics with `parseInt(..., 10)` or `parseFloat(...)`\n- Call `loadConfig()` once at module load in index.ts: `const config = loadConfig();`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Logger Usage Pattern\n\n**Import:**\n```typescript\nimport { logger } from \"../logger.js\";\n```\n\n**Interface:**\n```typescript\nexport const logger = {\n  debug(message: string, fields?: Record<string, unknown>): void,\n  info(message: string, fields?: Record<string, unknown>): void,\n  warn(message: string, fields?: Record<string, unknown>): void,\n  error(message: string, fields?: Record<string, unknown>): void,\n};\n```\n\n**Usage examples:**\n```typescript\n// From settlement.ts:73-80\nlogger.info(\"settlement worker detected locked round\", {\n  pda,\n  creator: round.creator,\n  targetSlot: targetSlot.toString(),\n  currentSlot,\n  slotTime,\n  game: round.game,\n});\n\n// From create.ts:115-119\nlogger.info(\"coinflip create requested\", {\n  wallet: body.wallet,\n  amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n  side: body.side,\n});\n\n// Error logging\nlogger.error(\"settlement worker poll error\", {\n  error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),\n});\n```\n\n**Output format:**\n- JSON to stdout (info/debug/warn)\n- JSON to stderr (error)\n- Fields: `{ timestamp: string, level: LogLevel, message: string, ...fields }`\n- No secrets or private keys in logs\n\n---\n\n### 7. Database Client Interface (db.ts)\n\n**Export type:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  // Rounds\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\n  deleteRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<boolean>;\n  updateRoundPhase(pda: string, newPhase: RoundPhase, updates?: Partial<...>): Promise<Round>;\n  updateRoundEntries(pda: string, entries: Array<...>): Promise<Round>;\n  getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  getRoundByMatchId(matchId: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  getRoundsByPhase(phase: RoundPhase): Promise<Round[]>;\n  getRecentSettledRounds(game: string, limit: number): Promise<Round[]>;\n  getUnsettledStats(): Promise<{ count: number; oldestAgeSeconds: number }>;\n  \n  // Operator audit log\n  insertOperatorEvent(pda: string | null, eventType: OperatorEventType, payload?: unknown): Promise<OperatorEvent>;\n  getLatestOperatorEvent(pda: string, eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<OperatorEvent | undefined>;\n  getLatestOperatorEventsForPdas(pdas: string[], eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<Map<string, OperatorEvent>>;\n  \n  // Close Call rounds\n  insertCloseCallRound(params: InsertCloseCallRoundParams): Promise<CloseCallRound>;\n  getCloseCallRound(roundId: string): Promise<CloseCallRound | undefined>;\n  getCloseCallCurrentRound(): Promise<CloseCallRound | undefined>;\n  getCloseCallHistory(limit: number): Promise<CloseCallRound[]>;\n  settleCloseCallRound(roundId: string, updates: {...}): Promise<CloseCallRound>;\n  \n  // Transactions\n  insertTransaction(params: InsertTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n  insertTransactions(params: InsertTransactionParams[]): Promise<void>;\n  getTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<Transaction[]>;\n  \n  close(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n**Creation:**\n```typescript\nexport function createDb(databaseUrl: string): Db {\n  const sql = postgres(databaseUrl);\n  return {\n    async insertRound(params) { ... },\n    async getRoundByPda(pda) { ... },\n    // ... all other methods\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Summary Table: Key Type Signatures\n\n| Item | Type/Signature | Import |\n|------|---|---|\n| Postgres client | `postgres.Sql<{}>` | `import postgres from \"postgres\"` |\n| Transaction handle | `postgres.TransactionSql` | Returned from `sql.begin(async (tx) => ...)` |\n| Logger | `{ debug, info, warn, error }` | `import { logger } from \"./logger.js\"` |\n| Config | `Config` interface | `import { loadConfig } from \"./config.js\"` |\n| DB client | `Db` interface | `import { createDb } from \"./db.js\"` |\n| Auth DB | `AuthDb` interface | `import { createAuthDb } from \"./auth-db.js\"` |\n| Round | `Round` interface | From `db.ts` types |\n| Operator Event | `OperatorEvent` interface | From `db.ts` types |\n\n---\n\n### 9. Common Routes Pattern (routes/)\n\nEach route file exports a factory function that returns a Hono sub-router:\n\n```typescript\n// From routes/create.ts\nexport function createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n  \n  app.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n    // Handle request\n  });\n  \n  return app;\n}\n\n// Usage in index.ts:171-174\napp.route(\n  \"/fairness/coinflip\",\n  createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher }),\n);\n```\n\n---\n\nThis covers all the essential patterns for creating a new queue module. The key takeaways:\n\n1. **Postgres client** is passed around as `postgres.Sql` instance\n2. **Transactions** use `sql.begin(async (tx) => { ... })`\n3. **INSERTs** use template-literal backticks with `RETURNING *`\n4. **Workers** are created via factories, stored, and started with `.start()`\n5. **Config** is loaded once via `loadConfig()` at startup\n6. **Logging** is structured JSON via the logger singleton\n7. **DB client** wraps postgres with typed query functions"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a74d2703fb7e32563 (use SendMessage with to: 'a74d2703fb7e32563' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63041\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 107486</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f29ae509-f643-4ea1-906d-d19d18bc6bbf","uuid":"69a2962d-e496-4922-939b-9529411c3207","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:09:05.563Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the backend codebase patterns for creating a new queue module. Please explore:\n\n1. `services/backend/src/` — what's the overall structure? List key files/dirs.\n2. How is the postgres DB client used? Find the `sql` import and transaction patterns (e.g., `sql.begin(async (tx) => { ... })`). What's the type of the transaction handle?\n3. Look at an existing INSERT statement to understand the SQL template literal pattern used.\n4. Check `services/backend/src/index.ts` for how workers are initialized.\n5. Check `services/backend/src/config.ts` for how env vars are parsed.\n6. Check the logger import/usage pattern.\n\nBe thorough — I need exact import paths, type signatures, and patterns to replicate.","agentId":"a74d2703fb7e32563","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a final comprehensive summary document. Here's everything you need:\n\n---\n\n## Backend Codebase Patterns Guide\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\nservices/backend/src/\n├── index.ts                 # Main app initialization (Hono setup, workers, routes)\n├── config.ts               # Environment var parsing & Config type\n├── db.ts                   # Database client (Postgres operations)\n├── db-config.ts            # Schema management utilities\n├── auth-db.ts              # Auth-specific DB operations (challenges, refresh tokens)\n├── logger.ts               # Structured JSON logger\n├── fairness.ts             # Fairness logic (secret generation, commitment)\n├── hono-env.ts             # Hono environment type definitions\n├── migrate.ts              # Migration runner\n├── tx-builder.ts           # Transaction building utilities\n├── middleware/             # HTTP middleware (JWT, rate-limit, auth)\n├── routes/                 # HTTP endpoint handlers (create, lord, closecall, etc.)\n├── worker/                 # Background workers (settlement, pda-watcher, retry, etc.)\n└── __tests__/              # Test files\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Postgres DB Client Usage\n\n**Import Pattern:**\n```typescript\nimport postgres from \"postgres\";  // from package.json: \"postgres\": \"^3.4.0\"\n```\n\n**Creation in index.ts:**\n```typescript\nconst sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);  // Returns: postgres.Sql instance\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);   // Wrapped client with typed queries\nconst authDb = createAuthDb(sql);          // Auth-specific operations\n```\n\n**Type Signature:**\n- `postgres(databaseUrl: string): postgres.Sql<{}>` — returns a typed query executor\n- Each query is executed via the backtick-template-literal syntax\n\n**Transaction Pattern (sql.begin):**\n```typescript\n// From migrate.ts:84-90\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  // tx is of type: postgres.TransactionSql (same interface as sql, but transactional)\n  await tx.unsafe(content);  // Run raw SQL with IF NOT EXISTS\n  await tx.unsafe(\n    \"INSERT INTO _migrations (version, name) VALUES ($1, $2)\",\n    [migration.version, migration.name],\n  );\n  // On function return: auto-commits. On error: auto-rollback.\n});\n```\n\n**Type of transaction handle `tx`:**\n- `type: postgres.TransactionSql` (extends `postgres.Sql`)\n- Supports the same methods: `` await tx`SQL template` ``, `.unsafe()`, `.json()`, etc.\n- Automatic rollback on error; auto-commit on success\n\n---\n\n### 3. INSERT Statement Pattern\n\n**Basic INSERT with RETURNING:**\n```typescript\n// From db.ts:310-328\nasync insertRound(params) {\n  const rows = await sql<Round[]>`\n    INSERT INTO rounds (pda, game, creator, server_key, secret, commitment, amount_lamports, side, match_id, phase, entries)\n    VALUES (\n      ${params.pda},\n      ${params.game},\n      ${params.creator},\n      ${params.serverKey},\n      ${params.secret},\n      ${params.commitment},\n      ${params.amountLamports},\n      ${params.side},\n      ${params.matchId},\n      ${params.phase},\n      ${params.entries ? sql.json(params.entries) : null}  // JSONB column\n    )\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return normalizeRound(rows[0]!);\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Type annotation: `` sql<Round[]>` `` — declares return type\n- Parameter interpolation: `${variable}` — automatically escaped\n- JSONB values: `sql.json(data)` — special handler for JSON columns\n- `null` values: pass directly as `${null}` or `sql.json(null)`\n- Return clause: `RETURNING *` to get inserted row\n\n**Batch INSERT:**\n```typescript\n// From db.ts:551-564\nasync insertTransactions(params) {\n  if (params.length === 0) return;\n  const values = params.map((p) => ({\n    wallet: p.wallet,\n    game: p.game,\n    match_id: p.matchId,\n    tx_type: p.txType,\n    amount_lamports: p.amountLamports,\n    tx_sig: p.txSig,\n  }));\n  await sql`\n    INSERT INTO transactions ${sql(values, \"wallet\", \"game\", \"match_id\", \"tx_type\", \"amount_lamports\", \"tx_sig\")}\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotent INSERT:**\n```typescript\n// From db.ts:536-548\nasync insertTransaction(params) {\n  await sql`\n    INSERT INTO transactions (wallet, game, match_id, tx_type, amount_lamports, tx_sig)\n    VALUES (\n      ${params.wallet},\n      ${params.game},\n      ${params.matchId},\n      ${params.txType},\n      ${params.amountLamports},\n      ${params.txSig}\n    )\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Worker Initialization Pattern (from index.ts)\n\n```typescript\n// Line 148-159\nconst worker = createSettlementWorker({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  serverKey: config.serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  pollIntervalMs: config.workerPollIntervalMs,\n  onSettleReady: async (pda) => {\n    await retrySettler.attemptSettle(pda);\n    pdaWatcher.unwatch(pda);\n  },\n  isFinalized: (pda) => retrySettler.isFinalized(pda),\n});\nworker.start();  // Workers start with .start() method\n\n// Close Call clock worker example (line 163-168)\nconst closeCallClock = createCloseCallClockWorker({\n  connection,\n  serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair,\n  db: sql,  // Note: can pass raw sql instance OR wrapped db\n});\ncloseCallClock.start();\n```\n\n**Worker interface pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport interface SettlementWorker {\n  start(): void;\n  stop(): void;\n  readonly isRunning: boolean;\n  poll(): Promise<void>;  // Exposed for testing\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Environment Variable Parsing (config.ts)\n\n**Pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Config {\n  port: number;\n  databaseUrl: string;\n  dbSchema: string;\n  rpcUrl: string;\n  wsRpcUrl: string | undefined;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  cluster: string;\n  challengeTtlSeconds: number;\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: number;\n  // ... more fields\n}\n\nfunction requireEnv(name: string): string {\n  const value = process.env[name];\n  if (!value) {\n    throw new Error(`Missing required environment variable: ${name}`);\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nexport function loadConfig(): Config {\n  const dbSchema = loadDbSchemaFromEnv();\n  return {\n    port: parseInt(process.env.PORT ?? \"3100\", 10),\n    databaseUrl: applyDbSchemaToUrl(requireEnv(\"DATABASE_URL\"), dbSchema),\n    rpcUrl: requireEnv(\"RPC_URL\"),\n    wsRpcUrl: process.env.WS_RPC_URL || undefined,\n    serverKeypair: parseKeypair(requireEnv(\"SERVER_KEYPAIR\")),\n    jwtSecret: (() => {\n      const explicit = process.env.JWT_SECRET;\n      if (explicit) return new TextEncoder().encode(explicit);\n      // Derive from first 32 bytes of server keypair\n      const kp = parseKeypair(requireEnv(\"SERVER_KEYPAIR\"));\n      return kp.secretKey.slice(0, 32);\n    })(),\n    // ... defaults for all fields\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Use `requireEnv(name)` for mandatory vars (throws if missing)\n- Use `process.env.VAR ?? \"default\"` for optional vars\n- Parse numerics with `parseInt(..., 10)` or `parseFloat(...)`\n- Call `loadConfig()` once at module load in index.ts: `const config = loadConfig();`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Logger Usage Pattern\n\n**Import:**\n```typescript\nimport { logger } from \"../logger.js\";\n```\n\n**Interface:**\n```typescript\nexport const logger = {\n  debug(message: string, fields?: Record<string, unknown>): void,\n  info(message: string, fields?: Record<string, unknown>): void,\n  warn(message: string, fields?: Record<string, unknown>): void,\n  error(message: string, fields?: Record<string, unknown>): void,\n};\n```\n\n**Usage examples:**\n```typescript\n// From settlement.ts:73-80\nlogger.info(\"settlement worker detected locked round\", {\n  pda,\n  creator: round.creator,\n  targetSlot: targetSlot.toString(),\n  currentSlot,\n  slotTime,\n  game: round.game,\n});\n\n// From create.ts:115-119\nlogger.info(\"coinflip create requested\", {\n  wallet: body.wallet,\n  amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n  side: body.side,\n});\n\n// Error logging\nlogger.error(\"settlement worker poll error\", {\n  error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),\n});\n```\n\n**Output format:**\n- JSON to stdout (info/debug/warn)\n- JSON to stderr (error)\n- Fields: `{ timestamp: string, level: LogLevel, message: string, ...fields }`\n- No secrets or private keys in logs\n\n---\n\n### 7. Database Client Interface (db.ts)\n\n**Export type:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  // Rounds\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\n  deleteRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<boolean>;\n  updateRoundPhase(pda: string, newPhase: RoundPhase, updates?: Partial<...>): Promise<Round>;\n  updateRoundEntries(pda: string, entries: Array<...>): Promise<Round>;\n  getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  getRoundByMatchId(matchId: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  getRoundsByPhase(phase: RoundPhase): Promise<Round[]>;\n  getRecentSettledRounds(game: string, limit: number): Promise<Round[]>;\n  getUnsettledStats(): Promise<{ count: number; oldestAgeSeconds: number }>;\n  \n  // Operator audit log\n  insertOperatorEvent(pda: string | null, eventType: OperatorEventType, payload?: unknown): Promise<OperatorEvent>;\n  getLatestOperatorEvent(pda: string, eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<OperatorEvent | undefined>;\n  getLatestOperatorEventsForPdas(pdas: string[], eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<Map<string, OperatorEvent>>;\n  \n  // Close Call rounds\n  insertCloseCallRound(params: InsertCloseCallRoundParams): Promise<CloseCallRound>;\n  getCloseCallRound(roundId: string): Promise<CloseCallRound | undefined>;\n  getCloseCallCurrentRound(): Promise<CloseCallRound | undefined>;\n  getCloseCallHistory(limit: number): Promise<CloseCallRound[]>;\n  settleCloseCallRound(roundId: string, updates: {...}): Promise<CloseCallRound>;\n  \n  // Transactions\n  insertTransaction(params: InsertTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n  insertTransactions(params: InsertTransactionParams[]): Promise<void>;\n  getTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<Transaction[]>;\n  \n  close(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n**Creation:**\n```typescript\nexport function createDb(databaseUrl: string): Db {\n  const sql = postgres(databaseUrl);\n  return {\n    async insertRound(params) { ... },\n    async getRoundByPda(pda) { ... },\n    // ... all other methods\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Summary Table: Key Type Signatures\n\n| Item | Type/Signature | Import |\n|------|---|---|\n| Postgres client | `postgres.Sql<{}>` | `import postgres from \"postgres\"` |\n| Transaction handle | `postgres.TransactionSql` | Returned from `sql.begin(async (tx) => ...)` |\n| Logger | `{ debug, info, warn, error }` | `import { logger } from \"./logger.js\"` |\n| Config | `Config` interface | `import { loadConfig } from \"./config.js\"` |\n| DB client | `Db` interface | `import { createDb } from \"./db.js\"` |\n| Auth DB | `AuthDb` interface | `import { createAuthDb } from \"./auth-db.js\"` |\n| Round | `Round` interface | From `db.ts` types |\n| Operator Event | `OperatorEvent` interface | From `db.ts` types |\n\n---\n\n### 9. Common Routes Pattern (routes/)\n\nEach route file exports a factory function that returns a Hono sub-router:\n\n```typescript\n// From routes/create.ts\nexport function createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n  \n  app.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n    // Handle request\n  });\n  \n  return app;\n}\n\n// Usage in index.ts:171-174\napp.route(\n  \"/fairness/coinflip\",\n  createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher }),\n);\n```\n\n---\n\nThis covers all the essential patterns for creating a new queue module. The key takeaways:\n\n1. **Postgres client** is passed around as `postgres.Sql` instance\n2. **Transactions** use `sql.begin(async (tx) => { ... })`\n3. **INSERTs** use template-literal backticks with `RETURNING *`\n4. **Workers** are created via factories, stored, and started with `.start()`\n5. **Config** is loaded once via `loadConfig()` at startup\n6. **Logging** is structured JSON via the logger singleton\n7. **DB client** wraps postgres with typed query functions"}],"totalDurationMs":107486,"totalTokens":63041,"totalToolUseCount":17,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creatio