{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NLEYcjBTAriYUmrkiitajC","type":"tool_result","content":"  interface Sql<TTypes extends Record<string, unknown> = {}> {\n    /**\n     * Query helper\n     * @param first Define how the helper behave\n     * @param rest Other optional arguments, depending on the helper type\n     * @returns An helper object usable as tagged template parameter in sql queries\n     */\n    <T, K extends Rest<T>>(first: T & First<T, K, TTypes[keyof TTypes]>, ...rest: K): Return<T, K>;\n\n    /**\n     * Execute the SQL query passed as a template string. Can only be used as template string tag.\n     * @param template The template generated from the template string\n     * @param parameters Interpoled values of the template string\n     * @returns A promise resolving to the result of your query\n     */\n    <T extends readonly (object | undefined)[] = Row[]>(template: TemplateStringsArray, ...parameters: readonly (ParameterOrFragment<TTypes[keyof TTypes]>)[]): PendingQuery<T>;\n\n    CLOSE: {};\n    END: this['CLOSE'];\n    PostgresError: typeof PostgresError;\n\n    options: ParsedOptions<TTypes>;\n    parameters: ConnectionParameters;\n    types: this['typed'];\n    typed: (<T>(value: T, oid: number) => Parameter<T>) & {\n      [name in keyof TTypes]: (value: TTypes[name]) => postgres.Parameter<TTypes[name]>\n    };\n\n    unsafe<T extends any[] = (Row & Iterable<Row>)[]>(query: string, parameters?: (ParameterOrJSON<TTypes[keyof TTypes]>)[] | undefined, queryOptions?: UnsafeQueryOptions | undefined): PendingQuery<T>;\n    end(options?: { timeout?: number | undefined } | undefined): Promise<void>;","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f29ae509-f643-4ea1-906d-d19d18bc6bbf","uuid":"af77f5da-0e01-4ad1-8758-0e7f67c6fb2b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:14:11.569Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"  interface Sql<TTypes extends Record<string, unknown> = {}> {\n    /**\n     * Query helper\n     * @param first Define how the helper behave\n     * @param rest Other optional arguments, depending on the helper type\n     * @returns An helper object usable as tagged template parameter in sql queries\n     */\n    <T, K extends Rest<T>>(first: T & First<T, K, TTypes[keyof TTypes]>, ...rest: K): Return<T, K>;\n\n    /**\n     * Execute the SQL query passed as a template string. Can only be used as template string tag.\n     * @param template The template generated from the template string\n     * @param parameters Interpoled values of the template string\n     * @returns A promise resolving to the result of your query\n     */\n    <T extends readonly (object | undefined)[] = Row[]>(template: TemplateStringsArray, ...parameters: readonly (ParameterOrFragment<TTypes[keyof TTypes]>)[]): PendingQuery<T>;\n\n    CLOSE: {};\n    END: this['CLOSE'];\n    PostgresError: typeof PostgresError;\n\n    options: ParsedOptions<TTypes>;\n    parameters: ConnectionParameters;\n    types: this['typed'];\n    typed: (<T>(value: T, oid: number) => Parameter<T>) & {\n      [name in keyof TTypes]: (value: TTypes[name]) => postgres.Parameter<TTypes[name]>\n    };\n\n    unsafe<T extends any[] = (Row & Iterable<Row>)[]>(query: string, parameters?: (ParameterOrJSON<TTypes[keyof TTypes]>)[] | undefined, queryOptions?: UnsafeQueryOptions | undefined): PendingQuery<T>;\n    end(options?: { timeout?: number | undefined } | undefined): Promise<void>;","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AnkY3ESxzu8TYoGhHUkhJh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `Sql` has a template literal call signature (line with `<T extends readonly ...>(template: TemplateStringsArray, ...parameters: ...)`), but `TransactionSql` extends `Omit<Sql, 'parameters' | 'largeObject' | ...>`. Since `Omit` preserves the call signature (it only omits properties by key), the TransactionSql should still have the call signature...\n\nWait, actually `Omit` in TypeScript does NOT preserve call signatures. That's a known issue. `Omit` returns a type without the call signatures from the original interface.\n\nSo the solution is to use `postgres.Sql` as the type for the transaction parameter, which is less precise but works. \n\nI'm seeing this same pattern used elsewhere in the codebase too, like in `closecall-clock.ts` where the db parameter is typed as `postgres.Sql`. For the JSONB issue, `tx.json()` expects `JSONValue` rather than `Record<string, unknown>`, so I'll need to either cast the payload or use a different approach. Looking at how db.ts handles JSON inserts, I can follow that pattern to resolve the type mismatch.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":588,"cache_read_input_tokens":48659,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":588},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f29ae509-f643-4ea1-906d-d19d18bc6bbf","uuid":"9808dc8d-dc8a-4bd0-adb4-7098aa773dfd"}
